  "doc_id": "35663",
  "text": "As full-length NS2B contains membrane-bound segments, an important advance was made when a soluble NS2B-NS3 construct was obtained for the dengue virus protease by covalently linking NS2B to the NS3 protease (NS3pro) via a covalent Gly 4 -Ser-Gly 4 linker [CITATION_1] . The same approach led to soluble NS2B-NS3pro constructs of the WNV and Zika virus proteases [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . These constructs are enzymatically active and widely used for activity assays . There is no general agreement, however, whether the linked NS2B-NS3pro constructs are also the most suitable constructs for drug discovery.",
